# Web — Limerence Author Constructor

Rules for `web/` (Limerence-Author-Web-App). Main app code: `web/editor-app/`.

## Tech Stack

- **Framework:** React 19 + TypeScript
- **Build:** Vite
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS
- **State:** Zustand (`web/editor-app/src/store/`)
- **Graph UI:** React Flow (`web/editor-app/src/components/nodes/`, `edges/`)
- **Backend:** Supabase (`web/editor-app/src/services/`)
- **Testing:** Vitest (`web/editor-app/src/**/__tests__/`)

## Project Structure

```
web/editor-app/src/
├── components/     # UI — FlowEditor, Inspector, ProjectTree, nodes, inspectors
├── store/          # Zustand stores (storyStore, analysisStore, …)
├── services/       # Supabase CRUD, DataMappingService, AnalysisService
├── mappers/        # DTO ↔ domain mapping
├── hooks/          # React hooks
├── pages/          # Route pages (StorySettingsPage, …)
├── types/          # TypeScript types
└── utils/          # Pure helpers
```

## Layout Pattern

- **TopBar** — save/load, global actions
- **ProjectTree** (left) — book/chapter/stats hierarchy
- **FlowEditor** (center) — React Flow graph
- **Inspector** (right) — selected node properties
- Resizable panels: `react-resizable-panels`

## Services Layer

| Service | Role |
|---------|------|
| `StoryService` | Story CRUD |
| `CreateService` | Entity creation |
| `UpdateService` | Entity updates |
| `DatabaseOperationsService` | Batch DB ops |
| `DataMappingService` | DTO mapping |
| `AnalysisService` | Validation, graph analysis |
| `MonetizationService` | Price tiers, story/chapter monetization |
| `AuthorAnalyticsService` | Author-facing analytics |

Services talk to Supabase; schema lives in umbrella `supabase/migrations/`.

## Code Style

- Functional components, named exports preferred
- Co-locate tests in `__tests__/` next to source
- Pure logic in `utils/` and `mappers/` — unit testable
- Types in `types/` and `services/dto/DatabaseDTOs.ts`

## Monetization (Constructor)

Source of truth: `docs/monetization/`. Detailed docs: `docs/constructor/`.

### Product rules

- **SKU:** Story Pass (platform sub), Полный доступ (`full_story`), Chapter Pass only
- **No per-variant IAP** — premium choices via sub or Pass; always offer free alternative variant
- Authors pick **price tier** from `iap_price_tiers`, never arbitrary price or manual product id
- **Free read by default** — `requires_pass_to_read` blocks reading without Pass

### Entitlement priority

`full_story` > `chapter_pass` > `subscription` (Story Pass) > free path

### DB fields

- `story_monetization`: `full_story_tier_key`, `requires_pass_to_read`
- `chapter_monetization`: `chapter_pass_tier_key`, `requires_pass_to_read`, `subscriber_early_access_days`
- `Variant`: `is_premium` only in UI (no per-choice tier)

### Validation (AnalysisService)

- Premium dialog MUST have at least one non-premium variant
- Warn if full_story tier < sum of chapter tiers (non-blocking)

### UI

- Story settings route: `/story/:id/settings/monetization`
- Tier dropdowns from `MonetizationService.fetchTiers(sku_type)`
- Do not enable free-form price inputs
- Chapter release: `chapterRelease.ts` + `subscriber_early_access_days`

